    <h1>TestOrg GitHub Security Posture Overview</h1>

    <div class="meta">
        <p><strong>Date:</strong> 2026-04-09 12:00 UTC · <strong>Run:</strong> test-run-id · <strong>Scope:</strong> 1 total · 1 non-archived · 0 archived repositories in
            <code>TestOrg</code></p>
    </div>

    <h2>Summary</h2>

    <p>This report provides an executive snapshot of how consistently core repository security controls
        are applied across 1 non-archived repositories in <code>TestOrg</code>
        GitHub organization.
        It measures how consistently key security controls are enabled, owned, and monitored across all
        non-archived repositories, using aggregated results only.</p>

    <h3>Observability Metrics</h3>

    <p class="question">Do we communicate to external parties how to inform us about security issues found in our public
        repositories?</p>
    <p><code>Security Policy Coverage</code>: <span class="metric">66.7% (2/3)</span>
        <em>(non-archived public repos only)</em></p>

    <p class="question">Do we have Dependabot security updates enabled so GitHub can automatically open remediation pull
        requests for vulnerable dependencies?</p>
    <p><code>Dependabot Status</code>: <span class="metric">60.0% (3/5)</span></p>

    <p class="question">Do we scan our repositories for leaked secrets?</p>
    <p><code>Secret Scanning Coverage</code>: <span class="metric">80.0% (4/5)</span>
    </p>

    <h3>Ownership Metrics</h3>

    <p class="question">Do we enforce branch protection rules?</p>
    <p><code>Branch Protection</code>: <span class="metric">60.0% (3/5)</span></p>

    <p class="question">Do we have CODEOWNERS files in <code>.github/CODEOWNERS</code> or
        <code>./CODEOWNERS</code>?</p>
    <p><code>CODEOWNERS Coverage</code>: <span class="metric">80.0% (4/5)</span></p>

